  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      H. Pylori is frequently observed in patients with irritable bowel syndrome(IBS). However, the&#xD;
      effect of H. pylori eradication on IBS is not clear.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patients with IBS symptoms using Rome IV criteria will be included. Testing for H. pylori&#xD;
      will be done. Patients with H. pylori will receive triple therapy and followed after two&#xD;
      weeks for eradication and assessment of IBS symptoms.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
